# Shadcn UI / Base UI Rules for This Project

## Avoiding Nested Buttons

### Button with Link
Don't write asChild in Button:
```tsx
// Incorrect
<Button asChild>
  <Link href="/dashboard">
    Dashboard
  </Link>
</Button>

// Correct
<Button>
  <Link href="/dashboard">
    Dashboard
  </Link>
</Button>
```

### Dropdown/Dialog/Alert Triggers
To prevent hydration errors from nested `<button>` elements, use the `render` prop on trigger components (like `DropdownMenuTrigger`, `AlertDialogTrigger`, etc.) when the trigger itself should be a styled button.

**Correct Usage:**
Pass the button component you want to use as the trigger to the `render` prop. The children of the trigger will be rendered inside that button.

```tsx
// Correct: Use `render` prop on the Trigger
<DropdownMenu>
  <DropdownMenuTrigger render={<Button variant="ghost" size="icon" />}>
    <MoreHorizontal />
  </DropdownMenuTrigger>
  <DropdownMenuContent>
    {/* ... */}
  </DropdownMenuContent>
</DropdownMenu>
```

**Incorrect Usage:**
Avoid `asChild` on triggers (as it can lead to nested buttons or unrecognized prop errors with this project's Base UI components) and do not wrap a button component directly.

```tsx
// Incorrect: Causes nested <button> error
<DropdownMenuTrigger>
  <Button>Trigger</Button>
</DropdownMenuTrigger>

// Incorrect: `asChild` causes nested buttons 
<DropdownMenuTrigger asChild>
  <Button>Trigger</Button>
</DropdownMenuTrigger>
```

## Cards and Overflow

### Dropdown Menus Inside Cards
When placing dropdown menus inside Cards, the dropdown may be clipped by the card's overflow. Solutions:

1. **Use higher z-index** on the dropdown (z-[100] or higher)
2. **Remove the Card wrapper** and use a simple div with border instead:
```tsx
// Instead of Card
<div className="border rounded-lg p-6 space-y-4">
  <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold">Title</h3>
  <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Description</p>
  
  <div className="relative">
    <DropdownMenu>
      <DropdownMenuTrigger render={<Button variant="outline" size="sm" />}>
        Options <ChevronDown className="ml-2 h-4 w-4" />
      </DropdownMenuTrigger>
      <DropdownMenuContent className="z-[100]">
        {/* Menu items */}
      </DropdownMenuContent>
    </DropdownMenu>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Flag Icons

Use the `flag-icons` library for country flags:
```tsx
import "flag-icons/css/flag-icons.min.css";

// Usage
<span className="fi fi-in" /> {/* India */}
<span className="fi fi-us" /> {/* USA */}
<span className="fi fi-cn" /> {/* China */}
<span className="fi fi-jp" /> {/* Japan */}
<span className="fi fi-eu" /> {/* EU */}
```

## ScrollArea and Refs

`ScrollArea` from this project's UI components doesn't accept a `ref` prop directly. Wrap the content in a div with the ref:

```tsx
// Incorrect
<ScrollArea ref={scrollRef}>
  {content}
</ScrollArea>

// Correct
<ScrollArea>
  <div ref={scrollRef}>
    {content}
  </div>
</ScrollArea>
```

## yahoo-finance2 Library

Always instantiate the class:
```typescript
import YahooFinance from "yahoo-finance2";
const yahooFinance = new YahooFinance({ suppressNotices: ['yahooSurvey'] });
const quote = await yahooFinance.quote("AAPL");
```

## Convex Auth

Always import `getAuthUserId` from `@convex-dev/auth/server`:
```typescript
import { getAuthUserId } from "@convex-dev/auth/server";
const userId = await getAuthUserId(ctx);
```
